args: So I push in the center of the dough,\nlayer on jam, then bake the cookies\nuntil they're golden brown... Perfect!
Hee hee! Oh, I do hope Elly likes these.
Hello, Elly! I see you've been training hard.
Ah, Julietta. What brings you here?
I thought you might want something\nsweet after all that exercise.
I've never made cookies before,\nso I hope they turned out all right.
Then permit me to try one. *munch*\nAh, but they are wonderful!
I am ever so fortunate to be adored by\nsomeone like you!
...Hee hee! I hope it goes just like that!
Now then! Elly is usually training here at\nthis time of day, sooo... Ah! There she is!
It looks like she'll be finished soon.\nI'll just call out to her and...
Er, wait. Are these cookies REALLY fit\nto be handed over to her?
They look slightly lumpy and misshapen.\nAlso, I might have used too much sugar.
N-no! I can't let myself be disheartened!\nAnd yet, if I were to give her anything\nbut my very best...
Ugh... All this worrying has set my\nstomach off again...
Whew! All right, time for a res...\nOh. Hello, Julietta.
What is it? You're looking rather pale.
I...I am fine, I assure you.
You really don't look well, though.\nDo you want me to rub your back?\nOr get you some water?
(Urgh... I didn't come here to cause her\ntrouble!)
N-no, I really am perfectly fine.\nDon't worry yourself for my sake.
Oww! Running has just made my stomach\nhurt even more...
A-are you all right, Julietta?\nDo you have a stomachache?
Hmm. Is this one of those situations\nwhere I should do as I'm told, or where\nI should actually do the opposite...?
M-my room is really close if you'd\nlike to lie down for a bit.
Oh, I don't want to trouble anyo—owwww!
This is no time to be acting tough!
That is NOT what I am doing here!
You say that, but your eyes are teary.\nStop being stupid about this already!
Willingly choosing to suffer by refusing\nto put pride aside for even a moment is\nstupidity personified!
Eeek! I...I'm sorry! I wasn't intending to\ninsult or belittle you! I, um, just...er...
L-let's just go to my room, all right?
Yes, thank you. I'm much better.
I'm sorry about calling you stupid.
Please don't worry about it.\nWhat you said was true.
I brought all of this on myself by worrying\nabout nothing, and caused someone I\nadmire undue anxiety in the process.
Eeep! Please forget I said any of that.\nNow then, I fear I must be going.
Oh, I think you dropped something.\nWait, are these...cookies?
Er, yes. Could I trouble you to please\ndispose of them for me?
But you've wrapped them up so nicely!\nThey're a present, right?
Oh, okay. ...Can I eat them, then?
No they aren't. They're overly sweet\nand horribly misshapen.
You don't need to lie to avoid hurting my\nfeelings. I can handle the truth.
B-but...it's the truth. They really ARE good.\nI'm really not lying—it's just, um, what\nI mean is...
Well, what is it? Hurry up and say\nwhat you want to say!
They taste good so maybe you should have\nmore confidence in yourself, geez!
It's obvious you were planning on giving\nthese to someone you admire when you\nlost confidence and abandoned the plan.
But the thing is, I KNOW that person would\nhave been really happy to receive them...
Are you trying to console me?
Right then! I'm going to make cookies—\nand this time I WILL deliver them!
It's still possible I might fail. So if I do...
Would you mind if I came here and\ngrumbled to you about it?
In that case, I shall stuff you full of cookies\nand gripe until the dawn!
